Due to the sign confusion of the skew quad. In MAD, we have two versions of transport matrix (TM).
Due to the sign confusion of the skew quad. In MAD, we have two versions
of transport matrix (TM).

Why ? We all agreed that the skew quads should have “north pole” at the top. Though Steve thought he had “north pole” at the top in his MAD model, Phil has shown/convinced Steve that he didn’t have the “north pole” at the top for the skew in his TM of June-10-2011. That’s why Steve made the change and produced TM of July-28-2011, which has larger cross-terms. This is understood for the blue as the optimal (minimum cross-term) setting was not achieved /used (as it’s small at 6 o’clock and much larger at other places of the RHIC ring).
